<% content_for :title, 'CV' %>

<div class="hresume">
  <h1>CV</h1>

  <h2 class="u-hiddenVisually">Profile</h2>
  <p class="u-textLead summary">I've been building websites professionally for
    over seven years and I specialise in HTML, CSS and JavaScript. I'm passionate
    about the latest web technologies and writing great code.</p>

  <h2 id="employment">Employment</h2>

  <div class="JobList">
    <% data.jobs.each do |job| %>
    <div class="JobList-item">
      <%= partial 'job', locals: { job: job } %>
    </div>
    <% end %>
  </div>

  <h2 id="skills">Skills</h2>
  <p>A selection of my recent experience in commercial and personal projects:</p>
  <ul class="u-listUnstyled">
    <% data.skills.each do |skill| %>
      <li class="Skill u-inlineBlock"><%= skill.name %></li>
    <% end %>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="personal">Personal Projects</h2>

  <p>Maintaining <a href="http://simonsmith.io">a blog</a> on various technical topics, focused around front end development</p>

  <p>Contributed a few <a href="https://github.com/postcss/postcss">PostCSS</a> plugins <a href="https://github.com/search?q=user%3Asimonsmith+postcss-">on Github</a></p>

  <p>Used React and SUIT CSS to <a href="https://github.com/simonsmith/github-user-search/">create a small app</a> that allows searching the GitHub user API.
    This was mainly a way for me to learn React and Flux.</p>

  <p>Creating, owning and maintaining a level design community -
    <a href="http://www.interlopers.net">interlopers.net</a>. The site has
  been running for over 10 years and is a recognised resource for Source engine
  development. Currently rewriting and redesigning the site on the
  <a href="http://laravel.com">Laravel framework</a></p>

  <p>Acted as a reviewer for <a href="https://twitter.com/tbrd">Tom Hamshere</a>'s
    book on <a href="http://goo.gl/DznlPd">Twitter's Flight library</a>. This
